{"title": "Spiked Blood", "content": "Vampires may have their differences across media, but most of them have something in common: they drink blood. They drink blood from humans (or whatever species they once were) usually. So, what happens when they feed off of someone with drugs, alcohol, or poison in their system?\n\nWhy, they get high, drunk, or poisoned of course.\n\nThis can be Played for Laughs (unless it's poison) since stoners and drunks are funny when they make fools of themselves. This is also the only logical way for vampires to get intoxicated since their diet mainly consists of blood.\n\nIn extreme cases, the vampire might actually get addicted to the tainted blood and deliberately seek out drug users or drunks.\n\nAs an extension, this can also apply to those who feed on humans, but aren't vampires. See Emotion Eater or To Serve Man for example. The latter overlaps with Assimilation Backfire.\n\nSee also Regret Eating Me. And no, this isn't about using blood with spikes as a weapon.", "url": "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SpikedBlood", "media_links": ["/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/BuffyTheVampireSlayer", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/SamuraiPizzaCats", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/Hellsing", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/Hellblazer", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/Runaways", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/TheDraculaTape", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/FredSaberhagen", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/Discworld", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/TalesOfMU", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/ThoseWhoHuntTheNight", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/Vampires", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/BloodsuckingFiends", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/EdgarAllanPoe", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/TheBloodyRedBaron", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/MorganvilleVampires", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/BretEastonEllis", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/TheInformers", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/CallahansCrosstimeSaloon", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/DoctorWhoExpandedUniverse", "/p